Rising musician Saxtee Vibes and his band were in their elements recently as they dished out a unique blend of African rhythmic percussion to fans in Cotonou. The occasion was at the 60th birthday celebration of Mrs. Chakira Abeni Wabi, a prominent and influential woman in the Benin Republic. Held at the Dream Beach Resort, Cotonou, the party which attracted dignitaries from Nigeria and Benin Republic, had Saxtee thrilling attendees with his singing prowess.   Okey Bakassi opens up on wish for stand-up comedy     Denrele Edun: I’ve not been lucky with love     NaomiBillz drops EP to celebrate birthday   Speaking on his sojourn, the talented singer said, “Performing live on stage is always my delight as a musician worth its salt and when I was contacted to perform at the occasion by the CEO of Sights and Crafts, a multimedia company based in Lagos, I knew it had to be a potpourri of grandiose and classy event and I have to bring my A-game to entertain all. “It was a good experience for me and my entire group members. I had fun and the Cotonou gig was a blast.” Amidst the euphoria of this event, Saxtee is set for a music tour that will see him and his band perform at Alujo Nite at Atlanta Event Centre Opera; Annual AHBCA Awards at Expo Event Centre, Houston, Texas; Ijoko Agaba Nite at Kings Banquet Hall, Milwaukee; Ankara Nite in Texas; and Annual Yoruba Cultural Festival in Howel, Miami.